Code by Eric Franzosa for the TEDDY genetics pilot.
Makes use of Eric's zopy codebase (https://bitbucket.org/franzosa/zopy).
Contact eric.franzosa@gmail.com with questions.

====

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Code for integrating and cleaning SNPs, mgx profiles, and metadata.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

./prep/metadata_clean.py
./prep/metadata_refactor.py
./prep/prep_genetics.py
./prep/prep_phlan.py

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Code for making derived microbiome properties
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

Compute BC distance between successive or initial time point for modeling

./prep/prep_bc_trends.py

Compute time of first acquisition for species x subjects

./prep/prep_acquisitions.py

Pull out major species for restricted modeling

./prep/prep_species.py

# ---------------------------------------------------------------
# Code for running models
# ---------------------------------------------------------------

# the code Eric used to actually run the models
# python script wrapping lme4 in R

./modeling/model_rpy2.py

# these were for subsetting the large inputs to make individual modeling runs faster

./modeling/subset_genetics.py
./modeling/chunk_rows.py

Code for working with USF cluster environment.
AnADAMA2 will streamline these steps so you can ignore them.

./slurm_usf/slurm_all.py
./slurm_usf/slurm.py

# this parses the raw output of the model into tables

./modeling/results.py

# ignore these; experiments that didn't work out

./modeling/model_pyper.py
./modeling/model_test.py
./modeling/model_statsmodels.py

